 and fourfold\n(TbMnO$_3$) periodic manganites. The basic difference is that the twofold\nperiodic magnetic structure is strongly inhomogeneous, that leads to large\n${\\bf P}$. On the contrary, the fourfold periodic magnetic structure can be\nviewed as a moderately distorted homogeneous spin spiral, which corresponds to\nweaker ${\\bf P}$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 4 Aug 2014 04:52:50 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-11-26"}
