{"id":"1408.0607","submitter":"Kicheon Kang","authors":"Kicheon Kang","title":"Locality of the Aharonov-Bohm-Casher effect","comments":"7 pages, 3 figures","journal-ref":"Phys. Rev. A 91, 052116 (2015)","doi":"10.1103/PhysRevA.91.052116","report-no":null,"categories":"quant-ph cond-mat.mes-hall","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  We address the question of the locality versus nonlocality in the\nAharonov-Bohm and the Aharonov-Casher effects. For this purpose, we investigate\nall possible configurations of ideal shielding of the overlap between the\nelectromagnetic fields generated by a charge and by a magnetic flux, and\nanalyze their consequences on the Aharonov-Bohm-Casher interference. In a\nclassical treatment of shielding, the Aharonov-Bohm-Casher effect vanishes\nregardless of the geometry of shielding, when the local overlap of\nelectromagnetic fields is completely eliminated. On the other hand, the result\ndepends on the configuration of shielding if the charge quantization in the\nsuperconducting shield is taken into account. It is shown that our results are\nfully understood in terms of the fluctuating local-field interaction. Our\nanalysis strongly supports the alternative view on the Aharonov-Bohm-Casher\ninterference that the effects originate from the local action of\nelectromagnetic fields.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 4 Aug 2014 08:29:21 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 20 Aug 2014 05:50:35 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 4 Feb 2015 01:30:50 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-03-17"}
